    // Overview
    overview_p1: 'Quiet Twitch automatically mutes your browser tab when a Twitch ad is playing and unmutes it the moment the ad ends. Multiple detection methods are used so the extension continues to work even when Twitch updates its player.',
    overview_p2: 'Additional features include:',
    overview_li1: '<strong style="color:#efeff1;">Mute inactive tabs</strong> \u2014 automatically mutes Twitch tabs you are not currently watching.',
    overview_li2: '<strong style="color:#efeff1;">Switch tab on ad</strong> \u2014 switches focus to another Twitch stream when an ad plays on your Primary Tab.',
    overview_li3: '<strong style="color:#efeff1;">Return when ad ends</strong> \u2014 switches back to your Primary Tab automatically once the ad is over.',
    overview_li4: '<strong style="color:#efeff1;">Close tab when stream ends</strong> \u2014 closes the tab when a broadcaster ends their stream, with a brief grace period to avoid false closures.',
